725042f-a.text:
14th Street, south of, adjoining, and at the S.E. corner of 26th Avenue, showing three old mansions. The second house from the right, adjoining the corner, is the Trowbridge house of 1873. 26th Avenue was formerly known after the family that owned the house. View 2 shows the Trowbridge house and the one south of it; view 3 also shows the Trowbridge house by itself; and view 44 the house at the S.E. corner of 26th Avenue, seen on the left in
view 1.
Views 1,2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  192S
Views 3,4:  P. L. Sperr
NO REPRCDUCTIONS  March 13, 1931
